  <ac:layout-section ac:type=\"single\">
    <ac:layout-cell>
      <p>Design stage. Gate D is the step between the product designing and actual development launch. The key purpose of this gate is to make sure that all major design considerations are done, and that all project management tasks which are vital for further project success are done. By this point the team is united in a common understanding of the goal of the project.</p>
      <p>Points from the checklist can be skipped/waived if it is judged to fit the project better. However, the decision about waiving points of the checklist must be made and agreed with the CTO or PD in time before the gate meeting is conducted. The argument for waiving a point must be stated inside the checklist along with the date of agreement and initials of the responsible.</p>
      <br/>
      <p>See a further description of each point here: <a href=\"https://<CONFLUENCE_HOST>/display/PMO/Draft+of+Gate+D+Description?src=contextnavpagetreemode\">Gate D Description</a>
      </p>
    </ac:layout-cell>
  </ac:layout-section>
